-- MORE: China Invests Total $28.2b in Indonesia Industry: Hidayat
-- B y   A g u s   S u h a n a
-- 2013-10-03T11:42:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-03/more-china-invests-total-28-2b-in-indonesia-industry-hidayat.html
Investments for 21 partnership
agreements by  China  during visit of President Xi Jinping,
Indonesia’s Industry Minister M.S. Hidayat says in Jakarta
today.
* Includes investment and financing in 300,000 ton-per-year
ferro nickel plant and related infrastructure in Sulawesi; three
other nickel smelters, three alumina smelters and related
infrastructure: statement
* Includes Garuda Indonesia signing financing agreement with
ICBC Financial Leasing Company Ltd, for five Boeing 777-300 ER
and six Airbus 320-200 aircraft, valued at $1.7b: statement
* Investment includes $1.8b loan agreement between Oki Pulp &
Paper Mills and China Development Bank Corporation for pulp mill
in south Sumatra: statement
* Includes agreement between Indika Energy and  China Railway
Group Ltd. (390)  to jointly develop resources and infrastructure in
Papua and Kalimantan: statement
* Includes agreement by Jakarta Monorail with China
Communications Construction Co. to help fund, design and build
project in Jakarta; and agreement with Sarana Infrastruktur
 Indonesia  on a monorail project for Bandung: statement
* NOTE: Indonesia yday signed agreements with China to develop
industries including fisheries, tourism and aerospace, the
presidential palace said, after meeting between Xi and
Indonesia’s President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono in Jakarta  To contact the reporter on this story:
